Name:          Alan Turing
Lived:         1912 - 1954
Nationality:   English
Field:         Computing
Known For:     Turing machine, codebreaking
Contribution:  Father of computer science; broke Enigma; Turing test for AI
Quote:         "We can only see a short distance ahead, but we can see plenty there that needs to be done."

Name:          Nelson Mandela
Lived:         1918 - 2013
Nationality:   South African
Field:         Politics
Known For:     End of apartheid
Contribution:  First democratically elected SA president; 27 years in prison; Nobel Peace Prize
Quote:         "Education is the most powerful weapon you can use to change the world."

Name:          Galileo Galilei
Lived:         1564 - 1642
Nationality:   Italian
Field:         Astronomy
Known For:     Heliocentrism, telescope
Contribution:  Confirmed Copernican model; law of falling bodies; faced Inquisition
Quote:         "And yet it moves."

