============================================================
  ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE & MACHINE LEARNING
============================================================

Concept:     Fine-tuning
Category:    Training technique
Definition:  Updates pre-trained model weights on task-specific data
Year:        2018
Researchers: Howard/Ruder (ULMFiT)
Applications:Customizing LLMs, domain adaptation
Related:     Supervised fine-tuning, PEFT, LoRA

Concept:     Backpropagation
Category:    Training
Definition:  Computes gradients via chain rule through network layers
Year:        1986
Researchers: Rumelhart/Hinton
Applications:Training all neural networks
Related:     Gradient descent, automatic differentiation

Concept:     Hallucination
Category:    Problem
Definition:  LLM confidently generates plausible but incorrect information
Year:        2020
Researchers: Many researchers
Applications:AI reliability, factual QA systems
Related:     Retrieval augmentation, grounding, calibration

============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Euler Polyhedron Formula
Branch:       Topology
Formula:      V - E + F = 2
Applications: Architecture, crystallography
Discoverer:   Leonhard Euler (1758)

Theorem/Law:  Four Color Theorem
Branch:       Topology
Formula:      Any planar map needs at most 4 colors
Applications: Cartography, graph coloring
Discoverer:   Appel and Haken (1976)

Theorem/Law:  Bayes Theorem
Branch:       Probability
Formula:      P(H|E) = P(E|H)P(H)/P(E)
Applications: ML, spam filters, medical testing
Discoverer:   Thomas Bayes (1763)

